🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ Why TCP is Reliable (Deep Insight 🔥)
Simple Idea

TCP is not just “reliable” — it uses multiple mechanisms together.

How TCP Achieves Reliability
Sequence numbers → correct order
ACKs → confirmation
Retransmission → resend lost packets
Sliding window → flow control
Mental Model 📦

Courier system with:

tracking number
confirmation call
resend if lost
WHY It Works

Because network is unpredictable:

packets can be lost
packets can arrive out of order

TCP fixes all these.

Interview Gold Line ⭐

👉 “TCP ensures reliability using acknowledgment, sequencing, and retransmission mechanisms.”

2️⃣ Why UDP Exists (Important Thinking)
Question

👉 If TCP is reliable, why do we even need UDP?

Smart Answer ✅

Because reliability comes with overhead and delay.

UDP is used when:

speed is more important
real-time data needed
Examples
video calls
gaming
live streaming
Key Insight ⭐

👉 “UDP sacrifices reliability for speed.”

Memory Trick

TCP = Safe
UDP = Fast

3️⃣ How Congestion Actually Happens
Deep Idea

Congestion happens when:

👉 Incoming traffic > network capacity

Mental Model 🚦

Too many cars → traffic jam

What Happens Internally
routers queue packets
buffers overflow
packets drop
TCP Solution
slow start
congestion avoidance
WHY It Matters

Helps prevent:

network collapse
high delays
Interview Tip ⭐

Always mention:
👉 “Buffer overflow and packet drop”

4️⃣ End-to-End Principle (Google-Level Concept)
Simple Idea

Most logic should be at end systems, not network.

Mental Model

Post office delivers parcels
→ doesn’t check content

Sender/receiver handle correctness.

WHY It Works
keeps network simple
improves scalability
Real Example

Internet routers:

don’t check application data
just forward packets
Memory Trick

Network = simple
Endpoints = smart

